# Project Conventions

## Naming

- Directories: kebab-case (`user-service`, `api-gateway`)
- Java packages: lowercase dot-separated (`com.example.auth`)
- Java classes: PascalCase (`UserService`, `OrderRepository`)
- Java methods/variables: camelCase (`findByEmail`, `isActive`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`MAX_RETRIES`, `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_MS`)
- Config files: kebab-case (`application-dev.yml`)
- SQL: snake_case for tables and columns (`user_account`, `created_at`)

## Project Structure

```
src/
  main/
    java/         # Application source code
    resources/    # Config files, templates, static resources
  test/
    java/         # Test source code
    resources/    # Test fixtures, configs
docs/             # Project documentation
.github/          # GitHub templates and workflows
```

## File Organization

- One public class per file
- Group by feature/domain, not by technical layer
- Keep related files close together
- Configuration in `resources/`, never hardcoded
- Tests mirror the source structure

## Code Style

- Maximum line length: 120 characters
- Use project formatter (EditorConfig, Checkstyle, or IDE settings)
- No trailing whitespace
- Files end with a newline
- UTF-8 encoding everywhere
- Consistent import ordering: standard library, third-party, project

## Dependencies

- Pin dependency versions explicitly (no dynamic ranges)
- Use BOM/dependency management for version consistency
- Review new dependencies for license compatibility and maintenance status
- Prefer well-maintained libraries with active communities
